\f0\fs24 \cf0 The Envelope Intersection and Variability-Based Test (EIVBT) analyses respiratory time series to detect intervals of periodic breathing, characterised by phases of nearly regular oscillatory patterns embedded within otherwise irregular respiratory signals.\
The detection process is built around a two-stage approach combining signal envelope intersection and filtering criteria.\
In the first stage, the algorithm identifies intervals using intersection points of the upper and lower envelopes of the time series. In the second stage, these intervals are filtered as either periodic or non-periodic using multi-condition logic.}